  "id": "019d286c-c8e3-7462-a4e5-a4c9d737c9d3",
  "content": "## Chunk 2: Phase 2 — Dashboard Graphed Document Reader\n\n### Task 2.1: Add new REST endpoint for entry neighbors\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `repos/corvia/crates/corvia-server/src/dashboard/mod.rs`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add `GET /api/dashboard/entries/{entry_id}/neighbors` route**\n\nThis endpoint goes in the dashboard module (`dashboard/mod.rs`) alongside existing routes like `/api/dashboard/entries/{entry_id}/history`. Uses `GraphStore::traverse` for multi-hop BFS traversal and returns neighbor entries. Uses the same `Result<Json<T>, (StatusCode, String)>` error pattern as existing dashboard handlers:\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Serialize)]\npub struct NeighborDto {\n    pub id: String,\n    pub content: String,\n    pub relation: String,\n    pub direction: String, // \"outgoing\" or \"incoming\"\n    pub score: Option<f32>,\n    pub source_file: Option<String>,\n    pub content_role: Option<String>,\n    pub source_origin: Option<String>,\n}\n\n#[derive(Deserialize)]\npub struct NeighborParams {\n    pub depth: Option<usize>,\n}\n\nasync fn entry_neighbors(\n    Path(entry_id): Path<String>,\n    Query(params): Query<NeighborParams>,",
  "source_version": "plans/2026-03-13-docs-workflow-impl.md",
